  "planContent": "# 🏗️ Architecture Blueprint\n\n## App Overview\nA high-fidelity, single-page interactive landing experience for the Porsche 911 GT3 RS, replicating the \"Stitch AI\" aesthetic. The application serves as a visual showcase of automotive engineering, utilizing a dark-themed, motion-focused layout to highlight performance specs and imagery.\n\n## Core Features\n- **Hero Display**: Full-viewport atmospheric banner with a gradient-overlay title.\n- **Performance HUD**: Data-grid component displaying core technical specifications (speed, power, acceleration).\n- **Kinetic Gallery**: Asymmetric grid layout for featured vehicle components (cockpit, wheels, aero).\n- **Performance Narrative**: Text-image pairing section detailing the vehicle’s engineering philosophy.\n- **Final CTA**: High-contrast, dual-action engagement module.\n- **Persistent Navigation**: Glass-morphism sticky header with responsive menu toggles.\n\n## UI & Layout Strategy\n- **Layout type**: Full-bleed responsive landing page.\n- **Header**: Sticky `glass-nav` (blur-2xl) containing the brand mark, centered logo, and utility nav icons.\n- **Main content area**: Stacked vertical sections following the provided Stitch design structure.\n- **Controls**: Primary CTA buttons use `primary-gradient`, secondary buttons use `surface-container-high`.\n- **Footer**: Brand-centric legal/utility footer with minimalist typography.\n- **Design System**: Strict Tailwind utility classes provided in the reference code (`primary-gradient`, `kerning-tight`, etc.).\n- **Color scheme**: Custom palette (e.g., `#131313` background, `#d5001c` primary-container, `#e2e2e2` on-surface).\n- **Responsive strategy**: Mobile (375px) uses a single-column layout with vertical stacking; Desktop (1440px) uses complex CSS grids for the kinetic gallery.\n- **Animations & UX**: Tailwind transitions on hover (`duration-700`, `scale-105`), subtle scroll-based content revealing.\n- **Touch Targets**: Min 44px height for all interactive buttons.\n- **Accessibility**: ARIA labels on all navigation items and images; `focus:ring-2` for all interactive elements.\n\n## Data Model & State\n| Variable | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| activeView | String | 'home' | Tracks current visible section |\n| menuOpen | Boolean | false | Mobile navigation toggle state |\n| imagesLoaded | Boolean | false | Triggers entrance animations |\n\n- **Persistence Strategy**: Stateless UI; state is derived from URL hash or component flags.\n\n## Technical Stack & Libraries\n- **Required CDNs**: \n    - `https://cdn.tailwindcss.com?plugins=forms,container-queries`\n    - `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap`\n    - `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:wght,FILL@100..700,0..1&display=swap`\n- **Allowed**: Tailwind CSS, Lucide Icons (as fallback for Material Symbols).\n- **APIs**: None (100% offline).\n\n## Implementation Steps\n1. Initialize HTML5 boilerplate with the specific Google Fonts and Tailwind configuration.\n2. Inject `<meta name=\"referrer\" content=\"no-referrer\">` into the head.\n3. Build the `header` with sticky positioning and the defined glass-morphism style.\n4. Implement the Hero Section: Add the background image with `referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer\"` and overlay the primary headline.\n5. Build the Performance HUD section using a flex-based grid for the stats.\n6. Construct the Kinetic Gallery with the specified asymmetric grid layout.\n7. Implement the \"Engineered for Excellence\" text/image pairing section.\n8. Build the Final CTA section with centered, high-contrast buttons.\n9. Create the Footer with the required legal links and copyright info.\n10. Apply all custom CSS styles (e.g., `.primary-gradient`, `.glass-nav`) into a `<style>` block.\n11. Add responsive breakpoints (`md:`) to adjust padding and layout scaling.\n12. Verify all image tags include `referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer\"` to prevent 403 errors.\n\n## Edge Cases & Error Handling\n- **Missing Images**: Set a fallback background color (`bg-surface-variant`) for all `<img>` containers.\n- **Small Screens**: Hide the \"Floating Caption\" on mobile to prevent content clipping.\n- **Accessibility**: Ensure all buttons have sufficient color contrast against backgrounds.\n- **Data Integrity**: All content is hardcoded as per the static design reference; no dynamic data risk.",
